The paper deals with theoretical guarantees of L1-analysis regularization when solving linear inverse problems. This involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The paper also mentions well-known regularizations such as the discrete total variation and the Fused Lasso, which are commonly studied in these sub-fields. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely ones for this paper.
